fr:mainmatter.fr:p:
Let C and D be categories and F,G:C\to  D be functors.
    A natural transformation \alpha :F\Rightarrow   G is 
    an assignment to every object x\in  C of a morphism \alpha _x:F(x)\to  G(x) in D,
    (called the component of \alpha  at x)
    the following diagram commutes in D:


      \usepackage {tikz-cd}
      \usepackage {amssymb}


        \begin {tikzcd}
            {F(x)} && {F(y)} \\
            \\
            {G(x)} && {G(y)}
            \arrow ["{F(f)}", from=1-1, to=1-3]
            \arrow ["{G(f)}", from=3-1, to=3-3]
            \arrow ["{\alpha _x}", from=1-1, to=3-1]
            \arrow ["{\alpha _y}", from=1-3, to=3-3]
        \end {tikzcd}
